<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Aban Hasan</title><link>https://www.abanhasan.net/</link><description>Recent content on Aban Hasan</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><lastBuildDate>Mon, 14 Jul 2025 13:28:19 +0530</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://www.abanhasan.net/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Grain, Vitality, and the Lamarckian Lens: An Essay on Diet, Environment, and Cultural Morphology</title><link>https://www.abanhasan.net/posts/grain-vitality-and-the-lamarckian-lens/</link><pubDate>Mon, 14 Jul 2025 13:28:19 +0530</pubDate><guid>https://www.abanhasan.net/posts/grain-vitality-and-the-lamarckian-lens/</guid><description>&lt;!-- Image Prompt: Header Image - An artistic, conceptual image blending imagery of wheat/grain, a DNA helix, and the silhouette of a human form, suggesting environmental inputs sculpting biology. -->
&lt;p>
 &lt;img src="https://www.abanhasan.net/images/grain-dna-morphology.png" alt="An artistic representation of grain and DNA shaping human vitality">
&lt;/p>
&lt;blockquote>
&lt;p>&amp;ldquo;The most emaciated, low-vitality cultures that racists berate eat the most grain.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p>
&lt;/blockquote>
&lt;p>This is an ugly observation. The kind of statement that hangs in the air, thick with the weight of unsavory history. The typical response is to recoil, to dismiss it as a crude stereotype and nothing more. But what if, instead of dismissing it, we dared to dissect it? What if we could flip this ugly statement from a tool of racial prejudice into a fruitful scientific question?&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Silicon &amp; Six-Shooters: AI as Manifest Destiny</title><link>https://www.abanhasan.net/posts/cowboys/</link><pubDate>Fri, 23 May 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://www.abanhasan.net/posts/cowboys/</guid><description>&lt;blockquote>
&lt;p>To be in software in 2025 is to be a cowboy in 1900. You&amp;rsquo;re living on the precipice of a bygone era, one that you barely comprehend is gone, as the industrial giants and their Pinkerton armies push you further west, towards an unknown horizon. The open range is closing, fences are going up, and the rules are changing. This isn&amp;rsquo;t just a shift; it&amp;rsquo;s a reckoning.&lt;/p>
&lt;/blockquote>
&lt;p>
 &lt;img src="https://www.abanhasan.net/images/cowboy_city.png" alt="A lone cowboy gazing at a futuristic city skyline">
&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Feeding the Hydra: Musings on Cyberslavery</title><link>https://www.abanhasan.net/posts/cyber-slaves/</link><pubDate>Sun, 13 Apr 2025 10:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://www.abanhasan.net/posts/cyber-slaves/</guid><description>&lt;p>Clarity.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>All we seek is clarity. Yet, it appears that everything around us – everything we see, everything we touch – is designed to be noisy, to disrupt every thought we have before it can fully form. Entire teams of researchers, scientists, psychologists devote their lives to finding and &amp;ldquo;pulling the right&amp;rdquo; switch in our minds, optimizing for engagement, for distraction.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Our inherent capital – the finite time and vibrant youth we possess – is systematically siphoned off to feed the mainframe, the ever-hungry digital systems that thrive on our attention.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>The War Against Heteronomy</title><link>https://www.abanhasan.net/posts/thewaragainstheteronomy/</link><pubDate>Mon, 31 Mar 2025 08:38:35 +0530</pubDate><guid>https://www.abanhasan.net/posts/thewaragainstheteronomy/</guid><description>&lt;p>
 &lt;img src="https://www.abanhasan.net/images/autonomy-header.jpg" alt="A person standing at a crossroads with multiple paths branching outward">
&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;em>Image: The Pathways of Choice - representing the autonomy that comes from recognizing our power to choose&lt;/em>&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="prelude">Prelude&lt;/h2>
&lt;blockquote>
&lt;p>Our Great War&amp;rsquo;s a spiritual war. Our Great Depression is our lives.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>— Tyler Durden, Fight Club&lt;/p>
&lt;/blockquote>
&lt;p>Recently, I came across a thread on X by the brilliant Andrej Karpathy, which made me reflect deeply on the nature of action and its relation to both individual fulfillment and collective progress.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Technofeudalism and the Return to the Real</title><link>https://www.abanhasan.net/posts/technofeudalism-and-the-return-to-the-real/</link><pubDate>Thu, 23 Jan 2025 12:34:29 +0530</pubDate><guid>https://www.abanhasan.net/posts/technofeudalism-and-the-return-to-the-real/</guid><description>&lt;p>What makes the modern manifestation of cloud capital, integral to the &lt;a href="https://thebeautifultruth.org/the-basics/what-is-technofeudalism/">Technofeudalism&lt;/a> system we live under, is that it&amp;rsquo;s impossible to go anywhere without having it glaring at you. It hovers above the heads of modern people like a cloud, taking all our attention and carefully curating it, effectively extracting life energy and transmuting it into data and narrative.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Nick Land extensively talks about hyperstition, and the memesis we see via social media enables false narratives to take on a life of their own, often manufactured by the techno-oligarchs themselves in service of their political ambitions.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Credentials &amp; Academic Journey</title><link>https://www.abanhasan.net/credentials/</link><pubDate>Mon, 15 Jan 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://www.abanhasan.net/credentials/</guid><description>&lt;script src="https://www.abanhasan.net/js/credentials-enhanced.js" defer>&lt;/script>

